Finnish Social Democrat Prime MinisterKalevi Sorsa and his centre-left majority government resignedformally, clearing the way for the Conservatives to re-entergovernment after 21 years in opposition.    The resignation was in line with tradition following theMarch 15-16 general election which gave the Conservatives ninemore seats and a current total of 53 in the 200-seat chamber.    President Mauno Koivisto asked the outgoing coalition ofSocial Democrats, Centrists, Ruralists and Swedish membersgovernment to stay on in caretaker capacity, officials said. REUTER&#3;